      "rationale": "PIV experiments were conducted at matched flow rates (2–6 LPM) and rotational speeds (2000–4500 RPM) using a blood analog fluid (water-glycerin mixture, 40% by weight). Temperature was maintained at 37 ± 0.5°C. Measurement uncertainties were quantified and reported."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., mean absolute error or validation metric u_val) documented and within acceptance threshold for velocity and pressure QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Velocity magnitude profiles at five axial planes were compared using mean absolute error normalized by bulk velocity. MAE ranged from 2.1% to 4.3% across operating points. Pressure head predictions agreed with experimental values within 5.8%, satisfying the 10% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
